#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn8.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn8.1:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 8 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 8 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn8.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Vaṅgīsavagga "
msgstr "1. With Vaṅgīsa "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn8.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Nikkhantasutta "
msgstr "1. Renounced "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts1ed1.185, pts2ed1.398, sc1
msgctxt "sn8.1:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn8.1:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā vaṅgīso āḷaviyaṃ viharati aggāḷave cetiye āyasmatā nigrodhakappena upajjhāyena saddhiṃ. "
msgstr "At one time Venerable Vaṅgīsa was staying near Āḷavī, at the Aggāḷava Tree-shrine, together with his mentor, Venerable Nigrodhakappa. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn8.1:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā vaṅgīso navako hoti acirapabbajito ohiyyako vihārapālo. "
msgstr "Now at that time Vaṅgīsa was junior, recently gone forth. He had been left behind to look after the dwelling. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn8.1:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā itthiyo samalaṅkaritvā yena aggāḷavako ārāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu vihārapekkhikāyo. "
msgstr "Then several women dressed in all their finery went to the monastery at Aggāḷava in order to inspect the dwelling. "

msgctxt "sn8.1:1.5"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato vaṅgīsassa tā itthiyo disvā anabhirati uppajjati, rāgo cittaṃ anuddhaṃseti. "
msgstr "When Vaṅgīsa saw them he became dissatisfied, with lust infecting his mind. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn8.1:1.6"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato vaṅgīsassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then he thought, "

msgctxt "sn8.1:1.7"
msgid "“alābhā vata me, na vata me lābhā; dulladdhaṃ vata me, na vata me suladdhaṃ; "
msgstr "“It’s my loss, my misfortune, "

msgctxt "sn8.1:1.8"
msgid "yassa me anabhirati uppannā, rāgo cittaṃ anuddhaṃseti, taṃ kutettha labbhā, yaṃ me paro anabhiratiṃ vinodetvā abhiratiṃ uppādeyya. "
msgstr "that I’ve become dissatisfied, with lust infecting my mind. How is it possible for someone else to dispel my discontent and give rise to satisfaction? "

msgctxt "sn8.1:1.9"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ attanāva attano anabhiratiṃ vinodetvā abhiratiṃ uppādeyyan”ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I do it myself?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn8.1:1.10"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā vaṅgīso attanāva attano anabhiratiṃ vinodetvā abhiratiṃ uppādetvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imā gāthāyo abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then, on the occasion of dispelling his own discontent and giving rise to satisfaction, he recited these verses: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn8.1:2.1"
msgid "“Nikkhantaṃ vata maṃ santaṃ, "
msgstr "“Now that I’ve renounced "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.1:2.2"
msgid "agārasmānagāriyaṃ; "
msgstr "the home life for homelessness "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.1:2.3"
msgid "Vitakkā upadhāvanti, "
msgstr "I’m overrun "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.1:2.4"
msgid "pagabbhā kaṇhato ime. "
msgstr "by the impudent thoughts of the Dark One. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn8.1:3.1"
msgid "Uggaputtā mahissāsā, "
msgstr "Even if a thousand mighty princes and great archers, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.1:3.2"
msgid "sikkhitā daḷhadhammino; "
msgstr "well trained, with strong bows, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.1:3.3"
msgid "Samantā parikireyyuṃ, "
msgstr "were to completely surround me; "

# NOTE: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/could-someone-with-a-copy-of-normans-elders-verses-help-me-out/3579/9
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.1:3.4"
msgid "sahassaṃ apalāyinaṃ. "
msgstr "I would never flee. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
#. VAR: etato → ettato (bj, pts1-2, mr) | ettako (si) | ettakā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn8.1:4.1"
msgid "Sacepi etato bhiyyo, "
msgstr "And even if women come, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.1:4.2"
msgid "āgamissanti itthiyo; "
msgstr "many more than that, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: byādhayissanti → byāthayissanti (?)
msgctxt "sn8.1:4.3"
msgid "Neva maṃ byādhayissanti, "
msgstr "they won’t scare me, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.1:4.4"
msgid "dhamme samhi patiṭṭhitaṃ. "
msgstr "for I stand firm in the teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.186, pts2ed1.400, sc5
msgctxt "sn8.1:5.1"
msgid "Sakkhī hi me sutaṃ etaṃ, "
msgstr "I heard this with my own ears "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.1:5.2"
msgid "buddhassādiccabandhuno; "
msgstr "from the Buddha, Kinsman of the Sun, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.1:5.3"
msgid "Nibbānagamanaṃ maggaṃ, "
msgstr "about the path going to extinguishment; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.1:5.4"
msgid "tattha me nirato mano. "
msgstr "that’s what delights my mind. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn8.1:6.1"
msgid "Evañce maṃ viharantaṃ, "
msgstr "Wicked One, if you come near me "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.1:6.2"
msgid "pāpima upagacchasi; "
msgstr "as I meditate like this, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.1:6.3"
msgid "Tathā maccu karissāmi, "
msgstr "I’ll make sure that you, Death, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.1:6.4"
msgid "na me maggampi dakkhasī”ti. "
msgstr "won’t even see the path I take.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
